caption: I’m giving two stars because the staff was really friendly and the host was really sweet. Other than that, I will not be going back to this place. They kept getting our order wrong to the point where I was embarrassed to keep sending the orders back so i just stayed quiet after the first two times since we had a party of 4. It was my boyfriends birthday and they even got the cake wrong. First they didn’t bring it at the beginning like I had requested during reservation, the name was wrong on the “special menu” but when it did come it was the wrong cake. I even went upstairs after I realized they weren’t bringing the cake and I told the friendly host about it and she had them bring it at the end of the meal but they still didn’t get it right. However they did comp the charge for the cake so I will give them that.

I visited the financial district location this past weekend while I was in New York and I was more than pleased per usual.  Everything was perfect and exceeded my expectations. The next afternoon the general manager of the restaurant even called me to make sure that was the case and I assured him it was. Above and beyond the call of duty, I also got great recommendations from my server Moe on a happening pub to go to for a relaxing Saturday night as well as where to get a great slice of pizza in Brooklyn on Sunday. Whoever reads this, make sure you tell Moe I said thank you, and I will definitely visit this location next time I am in in Manhattan.

Had dinner at Morton’s Steakhouse last night & it was really beyond what I had expected. From the minute I walked in the door until we left, everything was perfect. That said, this might my least favorite steakhouse out of 20 or so I've encountered in Manhattan (plus Peter Luger in Brooklyn).  I've been in a couple of flagship McDonald's franchises with better ambiance.  Most critically, the time from ordering to service was quite long for us, and on top of that, several of our steaks were overcooked, so we had to wait 3 times as long as other steakhouses to eat.  (For context, I most appreciate Wolfgangs, Keens, Sparks, Benjamin, Homestead, BLT, Delmonicos, and Luger.  Not as great a fan as Smith & Wollenskys or Palm as some of my pals.)

I am not sure why this chain of restaurants is so popular- I’ve been to 3 of them (NYC, Dallas and Miami) and the food was very average in each of them. Since it is a steakhouse, you would think that the steak is good over there. Nope. I would compare Morton’s to Outback Steakhouse. If you want an okay stay, you’ll probably be better off going to Outback since it is cheaper rather than to Morton’s, where the prices are on the same level with the majority of really good steakhouses, but the steak quality leaves much to be desired. If you happen to be in any of the Morton’s places, order Crab Cake - it is pretty good over there. He service is good though, the atmosphere is nice. The drinks are good as well.
